    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look for a strong offensive output today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest daily efficiency score of 83.29. His matchup against Kelly is an ideal setup; the combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park, a high batting order position, and a slow-delivering pitcher creates a premium environment for his speed, with an 87% projected SB success rate significantly boosting his outlook. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (71.35) and **Josh Jung** (64.50) also represent high-value starts. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** benefits from a substantial platoon advantage against the right-handed Keller, while **Josh Jung**\u2019s 14% skill-adjustment score reflects his current comfort level at the plate combined with a park factor that favors his power profile.\n\nOur most difficult decision of the day involved the benching of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, who missed the cut with a score of 54.42. Despite his high base expectation and solid xwOBA, the combination of an elite arm in Misiorowski and a slight park penalty pushed him behind the current starters, who generally possess more favorable platoon splits or superior defensive-run-environment matchups. Elsewhere, **Luis Robert Jr.** remains in the lineup despite a sub-50 score (43.38), as his speed-centric utility in a 5x5 format remains vital, even against a tough arm like Yamamoto. We are monitoring **Luis Robert Jr.** closely, however, as the combination of an elite hold pitcher and a negative platoon shift puts him right at our threshold for a \"Below floor\" designation. \n\nThe primary risk today is the volatility of the pitching matchups facing the outfield. Both **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** face McLean, an elite arm whose skill profile is suppressing their efficiency scores into the high 40s and mid-50s respectively. While the wind-out conditions at the stadium provide a small 5% bump for both, we are cautiously optimistic that the high-ceiling nature of these hitters will 